7. Conduct product and packaging research and development exclusively for the export of the Products, such as meeting
foreign regulatory 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
requirements and foreign buyer specifications and identifying and designing for foreign buyer and consumer preferences;

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
8. Negotiate and enter into agreements with governments and other foreign persons regarding non-tariff trade barriers
in the Export Markets, such as packaging requirements, establishing and operating fumigation facilities and providing
specialized packing operations and other quality control procedures to be followed by its Members in the export of
Products into the Export Markets; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
9. Advise and cooperate with agencies of the U.S. Government in establishing procedures regulating the export of
Members' Products, Services and/or Technology Rights into the Export Markets; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
10. Negotiate and enter into purchase agreements with buyers in the Export Markets regarding the export prices, quantities,
type and quality of Products, time periods, and the terms and conditions of sale; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
11. Broker or take title to the Products; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
12. Purchase Products from non-Member producers whenever necessary to fulfill specific sales obligations; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
13. Solicit non-Member producers to become Members; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
14. Communicate and process export orders; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
15. Assist each Member in maintaining the quality standards necessary to be successful in the Export Markets; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
16. Provide Export Trade Facilitation Services with respect to Products, Services and Technology Rights; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
17. Provide, procure, negotiate, contract and administer transportation services for Products in the course of
export, including overseas freight transportation, inland freight transportation from the packing house to the
U.S. port of embarkment, leasing of transportation equipment and facilities, storage and warehousing, stevedoring,
wharfage and handling, insurance, forwarder services, trade documentation and services, customs clearance, financial
instruments and foreign exchange; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
18. Negotiate freight rate contracts with individual carriers and carrier conferences either directly or indirectly
through shippers associations and/or freight forwarders; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
19. Arrange financing through bank holding companies, governmental financial assistance programs and other arrangements;

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
20. Bill and collect from foreign buyers and provide accounting, tax, legal and consulting assistance and services;

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
21. Enter into exclusive agreements with Non-Members to 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
provide Export Trade Services and Trade Facilitation Services; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
22. Design, implement and administer Foreign Sales Corporations in accordance with the Internal Revenue Code; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
23. Open and operate overseas sales and distribution offices and companies to facilitate the sales and distribution
of the Products in the Export Markets; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
24. Apply for and utilize applicable export assistance and incentive programs which are available within the governmental
and private sectors, such as the USDA Export Enhancement and Market Promotion programs; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
25. Negotiate and enter into agreements with governments and foreign persons to develop countertrade arrangements;

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
26. Refuse to deal with or provide quotations to other Export Intermediaries for sales of the Members' Products into
the Export Markets; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
27. Require common marking and identification of its Members' Products sold in the Export Markets; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
28. Exchange information with and among the Members as necessary to carry out the Export Trade Facilitation 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Services and Export Trade Activities and Methods of 
